recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease a 2-quart baking dish.', 'In a large bowl, beat together the eggs, sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and salt until smooth.', 'Pour into the prepared baking dish.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 1 hour, or until a knife inserted into the center of the pudding comes out clean.']

title: Apple chips
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350f.', 'Place apples in single layer on baking sheet.', 'Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.', 'Bake 15 min.', 'Or until apples are tender.']

title: Homemade pancakes
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.', 'In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg, milk, water and vanilla.', 'Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.', 'Heat a lightly oiled griddle or frying pan over medium heat.', 'Pour or scoop the batter onto the griddle, using approximately 1/4 cup for each pancake.', 'Cook until bubbles form on the surface and the edges are dry.', 'Flip and cook until golden brown.', 'Serve with butter and syrup.']

title: Peanut butter dog cookies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease cookie sheets.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and peanut butter.', 'Beat in the sugar and egg.', 'Dissolve the baking soda in the hot water.', 'Stir into the peanut butter mixture.', 'Combine the flour, salt and baking soda; stir into the peanut butter mixture.', 'Roll dough into walnut sized balls and place 2 inches apart onto the prepared cookie sheets.', 'Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in the preheated oven.', 'Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.']

title: Cheesy popovers
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Beat eggs, milk and butter in large bowl with whisk until blended.', 'Add flour, sugar and salt; mix well.', 'Stir in cheese.', 'Pour into 12 greased muffin cups.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until puffed and golden brown.']

title: Cinnamon sugar butter
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan.', 'Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until butter is melted and mixture is smooth.', 'Serve warm or cold.']

title: Homemade pancake mix
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, and salt.', 'In a separate bowl, whisk together the milk, egg, and vanilla.', 'Pour the milk mixture into the flour mixture and whisk until smooth.', 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Pour in the butter and swirl to coat the bottom of the pan.', 'Pour in the batter and cook until the edges are dry and the center is set, about 2 minutes.', 'Flip and cook until golden brown, about 2 minutes more.']

title: Bread machine basic bread
recipe: ['Add ingredients in order suggested by your manufacturer.', 'Select basic bread setting.']

title: Cranberry sauce
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine cranberries, sugar, orange zest, and salt.', 'Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.', 'Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, until cranberries pop and sauce thickens, about 10 minutes.', 'Remove from heat and let cool.']

title: Creamy onion dip
recipe: ['Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add onion and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir in cream cheese and milk.', 'Cook until cream cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir in sour cream, salt, and pepper.']

title: Dill sauce
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.', 'Cover and chill.']

title: Philly cheese steak sandwich
recipe: ['Spread cut sides of bun with cream cheese spread.', 'Fill with remaining ingredients.']

title: Creamy cheese sauce
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.', 'Whisk in flour and cook, whisking constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly, about 1 minute.', 'Whisk in milk and cream.', 'Bring to a boil, whisking constantly, then reduce heat to low and simmer, whisking constantly, until thickened, about 5 minutes.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Stir in cheese until melted.']

title: Spinach and tomato pizza
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 450 degrees f. roll out pizza dough on a lightly floured surface to a 12-inch round.', 'Transfer to a baking sheet.', 'Brush dough with olive oil.', 'Bake for 10 minutes.', 'Remove from oven and spread ricotta cheese over crust.', 'Top with spinach, tomatoes, garlic, salt and pepper.', 'Bake for 10 minutes.', 'Sprinkle with mozzarella and bake for 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.']

title: Red cabbage slaw
recipe: ['In a large bowl, whisk the vinegar with the sugar, salt and pepper.', 'Add the cabbage and apple and toss to coat.', 'Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.', 'Stir in the oil.']

title: Creamy cucumber salad
recipe: ['Toss cucumbers with cream cheese and dressing.', 'Top with remaining ingredients.']

title: Tomato and oaxacan cheese quesadillas
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes.', 'Add tomatoes, parsley, cilantro, salt and pepper.', 'Cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are soft, about 10 minutes.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Brush one side of each tortilla with oil.', 'Place tortillas in skillet and cook until golden, about 2 minutes per side.', 'Transfer tortillas to a plate.', 'Top each tortilla with 1/4 cup cheese, 1/4 cup tomato mixture, and 1 tablespoon parsley.', 'Fold tortillas in half and serve.']

title: Carrot and garlic pita bread
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'Cut the pita bread into quarters and place on a baking sheet.', 'Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 'Bake for about 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.', 'Remove from oven and set aside.', 'In a small bowl, combine the garlic, carrots and olive oil.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Spread the mixture over the pita bread and return to the oven for about 5 minutes, or until the pitas are crisp and golden.']

title: Peanut butter and cheese sandwich
recipe: ['Spread 1 bread slice with peanut butter.', 'Fill bread slices with remaining ingredients.']

title: Ham and cheese salad
recipe: ['Layer lettuce, ham, cheese, onions and peppers in large bowl.', 'Add dressing; toss lightly.']

title: Avocado salad
recipe: ['In a large bowl, combine the avocado, onion, lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper.', 'Toss gently to combine.']

title: Homemade gelato
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the sugar, water and salt and bring to a boil.', 'Cook over moderate heat, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.', 'Remove from the heat and let cool completely.', 'In a large bowl, whisk the egg yolks with the milk and the cooled sugar syrup.', 'Gradually whisk in the hot milk mixture.', 'Strain the custard through a fine sieve into a bowl, pressing on the solids.', 'Refrigerate until chilled, about 2 hours.', "Freeze the custard in an ice-cream maker according to the manufacturer's instructions.", 'Transfer to a freezer-safe container and freeze until firm, about 2 hours.']

title: Easy microwave caramel sauce
recipe: ['Put the butter in a heatproof bowl and microwave for 30 seconds at 500 w.', 'Add the sugar and water and mix well.', 'Add the egg yolk and mix well.', 'Add the salt and mix well.', 'Microwave for 1 minute at 500 w.', 'Mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds at 500 w. mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds.', 'Mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds.', 'Mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds.', 'Mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds.', 'Mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds.', 'Mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds.', 'Mix well.', 'Microwave for another 30 seconds.', 'Mix well.']

title: Hummus
recipe: ['Place all ingredients in a food processor and process until smooth.', 'Serve with pita chips, pita chips, or veggies.']

title: Deviled eggs
recipe: ['Cut eggs lengthwise in half.', 'Remove yolks; place in medium bowl.', 'Add mayo, mustard, onions and seasonings; mix well.', 'Spoon into egg whites.']

title: Pork chops with apples and onions
recipe: ['Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add chops; cook 4 min.', 'On each side or until done (145 degrees f).', 'Remove from skillet; cover to keep warm.', 'Add apples and onions to skillet; cook and stir 3 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in vinegar; cook 1 min.', 'Return chops to skillet; spoon apple mixture over chops.', 'Cook 2 min.', 'Or until heated through.']

title: Zucchini boats
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Place zucchini halves, cut-side up, on a baking sheet.', 'Drizzle with olive oil, and season with salt and pepper.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until tender, about 30 minutes.', 'Remove from oven, and cool.', 'Scoop out the flesh from the zucchini halves, and place in a bowl.', 'Mash with a fork.', 'Stir in the tomato, onion, garlic, and feta cheese.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Fill each zucchini half with the mixture.']

title: Corn and green onion soup
recipe: ['Heat oil in large saucepan on medium-high heat.', 'Add onions and garlic; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add corn and peppers; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until heated through.']

title: Chocolate cake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'Grease and flour a 9 x 13 inch pan.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla.', 'Combine the flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into the creamed mixture alternately with the water.', 'Pour into prepared pan.', 'Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes.', 'Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.']

title: Portobello mushroom and arugula flatbread
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. place mushrooms on a baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.', 'Season with salt and pepper.', 'Roast mushrooms for 1520 minutes, or until tender.', 'Remove from oven and set aside.', 'Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Add onion and garlic and cook for about 5 minutes, or until soft.', 'Add spinach and cook for about 2 minutes, or until wilted.', 'Remove from heat and set aside.', 'Place flatbread on a baking sheet.', 'Top flatbread with sauteed mushrooms, spinach, and goat cheese.', 'Bake for about 5 minutes, or until flatbread is crispy and cheese is melted.', 'Remove from oven and top with arugula and roasted red pepper.']

title: Apple & cheddar cheese bake
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Mix apples, onions and cinnamon in 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Add water; stir.', 'Cover.', 'Bake 45 min.', 'Or until apples are tender.', 'Stir in cheese; bake, uncovered, 5 min.', 'Or until melted.']

title: Zucchini and potato salad
recipe: ['Cook potatoes in boiling water in large saucepan 15 min.', 'Or until tender; drain.', 'Cool.', 'Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch-thick slices.', 'Place in large bowl.', 'Add zucchini, onions, peppers and tomatoes; mix lightly.', 'Mix dressing and cheese; pour over vegetable mixture.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.']

title: Red cabbage salad with manchego cheese
recipe: ['In a large bowl, toss the cabbage with the red wine vinegar, olive oil, garlic and crushed red pepper.', 'Season with salt and pepper and serve.']

title: Egg in a mug
recipe: ['Add water to mug; stir.', 'Microwave on high 30 sec.', 'Or until egg is set.']

title: Cinnamon cream cheese souffle
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. butter a 2-quart souffle dish.', 'In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.', 'Add the milk and eggs and beat until smooth.', 'Pour the batter into the prepared souffle dish.', 'In a small bowl, combine the cream cheese and butter.', 'Beat until smooth.', 'Pour the cream cheese mixture over the souffle.', 'Bake for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.']

title: Caramelized onion confit
recipe: ['In a large saucepan, melt the butter in the oil.', 'Add the onions and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until golden, about 20 minutes.', 'Add the sugar and cook, stirring, until caramelized, about 15 minutes longer.', 'Season with salt and pepper and let cool.']

title: Peanut butter cookies
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and peanut butter.', 'Beat in the sugar and eggs.', 'Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into the peanut butter mixture.', 'Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.', 'Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in the preheated oven.', 'Allow cookies to cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.']

title: Lemon and sugar syrup
recipe: ['Combine the sugar and water in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.', 'Cook, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved.', 'Remove from the heat and let cool.', 'Stir in the lemon juice and the simple syrup.']

title: Quinoa tabbouleh
recipe: ['Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan.', 'Stir in quinoa; cover, remove from heat, and let stand 5 minutes.', 'Fluff with a fork.', 'Combine quinoa, tomatoes, onion, parsley, mint, and oil in a large bowl; toss well.', 'Add lemon juice, salt, and pepper; toss well.']

title: Asparagus with parmesan
recipe: ['Melt butter in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add asparagus; cook and stir 3 to 4 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add broth; cover.', 'Cook on medium-low heat 5 min.', 'Or until asparagus is crisp-tender.', 'Stir in parmesan and pepper.']

title: Caramelized peaches
recipe: ['Melt butter in large skillet on medium heat.', 'Add sugar; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or until sugar is dissolved.', 'Add peaches; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until heated through.', 'Sprinkle with cinnamon.']

title: Caprese salad
recipe: ['Cut tomatoes in half, then cut each half crosswise into 4 wedges.', 'Arrange tomatoes, cut sides up, on platter.', 'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 'Drizzle with oil.', 'Sprinkle with cheese and basil.']

title: Crispy tortilla
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'In a shallow bowl, whisk together the egg and salt.', 'In another shallow bowl, combine the panko and parmesan cheese.', 'Dip each tortilla in the egg mixture, then coat with the panko mixture.', 'Place on the baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.', 'Serve with your favorite salsa.']

title: Mini brie galettes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400f.', 'Unfold pastry on lightly floured surface; roll to 12-inch square.', 'Cut into 12 (4-inch) squares.', 'Place 1 square on ungreased baking sheet.', 'Brush edges with egg; sprinkle with cheese.', 'Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.']

title: Lemon cinnamon bread
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease and flour a 9x5 inch loaf pan.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the lemon juice.', 'Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; stir into the creamed mixture alternately with the oil.', 'Pour batter into prepared pan.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 60 to 70 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the loaf comes out clean.', 'Cool in the pan for 10 minutes before removing to cool completely on a wire rack.']

title: Grilled pork chops
recipe: ['Mix all ingredients except chops.', 'Pour over chops in shallow dish; turn to coat both sides of each chop.', 'Refrigerate 30 min.', 'To marinate.', 'Heat grill to medium heat.', 'Remove chops from marinade; discard marinade.', 'Grill chops 5 to 6 min.', 'On each side or until done (145 degrees f).']

title: Bbq rib-eye
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium-high heat.', 'Mix barbecue sauce and pepper.', 'Grill steaks 4 min.', 'On each side or until medium doneness (160f), brushing occasionally with barbecue sauce mixture.']

title: Zesty radish salad
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients except dressing in large bowl.', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.']

title: Cilantro wonton cups
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350 degrees f.', 'Place 1 won ton wrapper in each of 24 mini muffin pan cups sprayed with cooking spray, extending edges of wrapper over top of cup.', 'Press edges of wrappers together to seal.', 'Bake 12 to 14 min.', 'Or until edges are golden brown.', 'Meanwhile, mix reduced-fat cream cheese, cilantro and oil until blended.', 'Fill won ton cups with cream cheese mixture; top with remaining won ton wrappers.']

title: Roasted red pepper butter
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'Place peppers on baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.', 'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 'Roast for 20 minutes, or until peppers are soft and blackened.', 'Remove from oven and let cool.', 'Once peppers are cool enough to handle, remove stems and seeds.', 'Place peppers in a food processor and pulse until smooth.', 'Add butter and pulse until combined.']

title: Fried onion rings
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'In a shallow bowl, whisk together the eggs and flour.', 'In another shallow bowl, mix together the bread crumbs, salt and pepper.', 'Dip onion rings in the egg mixture, then dredge in the bread crumb mixture.', 'Fry in the hot oil until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.']

title: Hibiscus iced tea
recipe: ['Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan.', 'Remove from heat and add tea bags.', 'Steep for 5 minutes.', 'Remove tea bags and add sugar, lemon juice and zest.', 'Stir until sugar is dissolved.', 'Chill until cold.', 'Serve over ice.']

title: Roasted butternut squash with garlic and onion
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 425 degrees f. toss squash with oil, salt and pepper.', 'Spread in a single layer on a baking sheet.', 'Roast for 20 minutes, stirring once halfway through.', 'Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft and golden, about 10 minutes.', 'Add squash and cook, stirring occasionally, until squash is tender and lightly browned, about 10 minutes.', 'Serve squash and onion mixture over couscous.']

title: Spinach and feta stuffed shells
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Cook and stir onions and garlic in hot oil in large skillet on medium heat 5 min.', 'Or until onions are crisp-tender.', 'Add spinach; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or just until wilted.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Stir in feta and pepper.', 'Spoon into shells; place in shallow baking dish.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until heated through.']

title: Sauteed greens with garlic and red pepper
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Add garlic; saute 30 seconds.', 'Add greens; saute 2 minutes.', 'Add salt and pepper; saute 1 minute.']

title: Chicken kabob dippers
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium-high heat.', 'Thread chicken onto 8 skewers alternately with peppers, onions and cilantro.', 'Grill 8 to 10 min.', 'Or until chicken is done, turning occasionally and brushing with dressing.', 'Serve with the remaining ingredients.']

title: Chicken and spinach pie
recipe: ['Heat oven to 375f.', 'Cook and stir onions in hot oil in large skillet on medium-high heat 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add mushrooms; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until tender.', 'Stir in spinach and chicken; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Or until heated through.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Stir in cheese and pepper.', 'Unroll dough on lightly floured surface; press into 9-inch pie plate.', 'Cut into 8 wedges.', 'Place in 9-inch pie plate sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Brush with egg; sprinkle with parmesan.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until golden brown.']

title: Pesto
recipe: ['Place all ingredients in a food processor and blend until smooth.', 'Serve with pasta, chicken, or vegetables.']

title: Shiitake mushroom soup
recipe: ['In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil.', 'Add the shiitake mushrooms and cook over moderately high heat, stirring, until softened, about 5 minutes.', 'Add the water and bring to a boil.', 'Simmer over moderate heat until the shiitake are tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Add the soy sauce and simmer for 1 minute.', 'Serve hot.']

title: Broccoli slaw
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients except cheese in large bowl.', 'Add cheese; toss to coat.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.']

title: Sweet & spicy ribs
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Place ribs in single layer in shallow foil-lined pan.', 'Mix barbecue sauce, sugar and pepper; pour over ribs.', 'Bake 1 hour.', 'Brush with barbecue sauce mixture; bake 30 min.', 'Or until ribs are done (160 degrees f).']

title: Peanut butter sauce
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the peanut butter, sugar, and salt.', 'Cook over moderate heat, stirring, until the sugar dissolves.', 'Add the lemon juice and cook, stirring, until the sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.']

title: Rice pilaf
recipe: ['Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat.', 'Add rice and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly toasted, about 2 minutes.', 'Add water and salt.', 'Bring to a boil.', 'Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer until water is absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 minutes.', 'Fluff with a fork and serve.']

title: Grilled beef fajitas
recipe: ['Heat grill to medium-high heat.', 'Mix steak sauce and salsa; set aside.', 'Grill steak 5 to 7 min.', 'On each side or until medium doneness (160f).', 'Cut steak across the grain into thin slices.', 'Top tortillas with steak, onions, tomatoes and cheese; fold in half.']

title: Crispy bbq chicken fingers
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Mix flour and seasonings in shallow dish.', 'Beat egg in separate shallow dish.', 'Dip chicken in egg, then in flour mixture, turning to evenly coat both sides of each strip.', 'Place in single layer on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until chicken is done (165 degrees f).']

title: Scrambled eggs with cheese
recipe: ['Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper in medium bowl with wire whisk until well blended.', 'Melt butter in 10-inch nonstick skillet until sizzling; add egg mixture.', 'Cook over medium heat, lifting edge with spatula to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath, until eggs are set but still moist.', 'Sprinkle with cheese.', 'Continue cooking, lifting edge with spatula and tilting skillet to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath, until eggs are set.']

title: Sweet potato and tomato sauce
recipe: ['In a large saucepan, combine the sweet potatoes, onion, tomato sauce, water, sugar and pepper.', 'Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until sweet potatoes are tender.']

title: Tofu with soy sauce
recipe: ['Cut tofu into 1 inch cubes.', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.', 'Add tofu cubes and cook, turning occasionally, until golden brown, about 10 minutes.', 'Drain on paper towels.', 'Stir soy sauce, salt, and pepper into tofu.']

title: Sesame garlic sesame dressing
recipe: ['In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic, and pepper.', 'Stir in the sesame seeds.']

title: Peppermint candy cane meringues
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 250 degrees f (120 degrees c).', 'Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'Beat egg whites in a bowl with an electric mixer until foamy.', 'Gradually add sugar, continuing to beat until whites are stiff and glossy, about 5 minutes.', 'Beat in peppermint extract and salt.', 'Fold in crushed candy canes.', 'Drop meringue by heaping spoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until meringues are dry, about 1 hour.']

title: Grilled skirt steak with balsamic vinaigrette
recipe: ['Light a grill.', 'In a small bowl, whisk the vinegar with the olive oil, lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.', 'Brush the steaks with oil and season with salt and pepper.', 'Grill over high heat, turning once, until medium-rare, about 8 minutes.', 'Transfer the steaks to plates and let rest for 5 minutes.', 'Thinly slice the steaks and serve with the vinaigrette.']

title: French onion soup
recipe: ['Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.', 'Add onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.', 'Add broth, water, thyme, salt, and pepper; bring to a boil.', 'Reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until onion is tender.', 'Stir in bread cubes.']

title: Rib-eye steaks with garlic and red pepper sauce
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add steaks; cook 4 min.', 'On each side or until medium doneness (160f).', 'Remove steaks from skillet; cover to keep warm.', 'Add peppers and garlic to skillet; cook and stir 2 min.', 'Stir in steak sauce; cook 2 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.', 'Serve steaks topped with sauce.']

title: Grilled chicken marinade
recipe: ['Mix all ingredients together.', 'Pour over chicken and marinate for at least 4 hours.', 'Grill over hot coals for about 10 minutes per side.']

title: Creamy cilantro rice
recipe: ['Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add onions and garlic; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in rice, broth, water and salt.', 'Bring to boil.', 'Reduce heat to low; cover.', 'Simmer 20 min.', 'Or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Let stand, covered, 5 min.', 'Fluff with fork.', 'Stir in cilantro and pepper.']

title: Grilled salmon with balsamic vinegar
recipe: ['Light a grill.', 'In a small bowl, combine the vinegar with the garlic, onion, salt and pepper.', 'Brush the salmon with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.', 'Grill over moderately high heat, turning once, until just cooked through, about 4 minutes.', 'Transfer the salmon to plates and serve.']

title: Patatas bravas
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400f.', 'Heat oil in large ovenproof skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add potatoes; cook 5 min.', 'Or until golden brown, stirring occasionally.', 'Add onions; cook and stir 3 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in garlic; cook 1 min.', 'Add broth; bring to boil.', 'Cover; simmer on medium-low heat 15 min.', 'Or until potatoes are tender.', 'Remove from heat; let stand 5 min.', 'Meanwhile, heat broiler.', 'Place potatoes in single layer on baking sheet; brush with oil.', 'Broil, 6 inches from heat, 3 to 5 min.', 'Or until golden brown.', 'Turn potatoes; brush with remaining oil.', 'Broil 1 min.', 'Or']

title: Philly cheese steak fries
recipe: ['Heat oven to 425 degrees f.', 'Place potatoes in large bowl.', 'Add oil; toss to coat.', 'Spread onto rimmed baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, turning after 20 min.', 'Meanwhile, beat eggs in medium bowl with whisk until blended.', 'Add onions, cheese and pepper; mix well.', 'Cut potatoes lengthwise in half; scoop out centres onto platter.', 'Top with egg mixture and bacon.']

title: Peanut butter blossoms
recipe: ['Heat oven to 375f.', 'Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.', 'Beat butter, peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in large bowl with mixer until light and fluffy.', 'Add egg and vanilla; mix well.', 'Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.', 'Shape dough into 1-inch balls.', 'Place, 2 inches apart, on baking sheets.', 'Flatten each ball with bottom of glass.', 'Bake 8 to 10 min.', 'Or until lightly browned.', 'Cool on baking sheets 1 min.', 'Remove to wire racks; cool completely.']

title: Peanut butter cupcakes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease 24 muffin cups.', 'In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.', 'Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the peanut butter and vanilla.', 'Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.', 'Fill the prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of a cupcake comes out clean.', 'Allow to cool in the pans for 10 minutes before removing to cool completely on a wire rack.']

title: Easy quesadillas
recipe: ['Spread 1 tortilla with cream cheese.', 'Top with salsa and shredded cheese.', 'Fold in half.', 'Cook in skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium heat 3 min.', 'On each side or until golden brown on both sides.', 'Cut into wedges.']

title: Easy cream cheese pie
recipe: ['Heat oven to 425f.', 'Beat cream cheese, sugar and cinnamon in large bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each just until blended.', 'Pour into crust.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until center is almost set.', 'Cool.', 'Refrigerate 3 hours.']

title: Bbq roasted carrots
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Place carrots in single layer on foil-covered rimmed baking sheet.', 'Mix barbecue sauce and pepper; brush onto carrots.', 'Bake 30 min., stirring after 15 min.']

title: Baked brie
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat.', 'Saute onion in butter until tender.', 'Stir in brie cheese, salt, and pepper.', 'Place brie mixture in a baking dish.', 'Bake in preheated oven until cheese is melted and bubbly, about 20 minutes.']

title: Kale chips
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 250f.', 'Toss kale with oil in large bowl.', 'Spread in single layer on large baking sheet.', 'Sprinkle with salt.', 'Bake 1 hour or until crisp, stirring after 15 min.']

title: Easy potato soup
recipe: ['In a large pot, combine the potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, broth, water and pepper.', 'Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.']

title: Creamy onion soup
recipe: ['Melt butter in large saucepan on medium heat.', 'Add onions; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add broth, water and seasonings; stir.', 'Bring to boil.', 'Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 15 min.', 'Or until onions are tender.', 'Stir in parsley.']

title: Cheesy stuffing
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Combine all ingredients except bread.', 'Spoon into 1-1/2-qt.', 'Casserole sprayed with cooking spray; cover.', 'Bake 40 min.', 'Or until heated through.']

title: Easy cheese cake
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease and flour a 9x13 inch pan.', 'In a large bowl, beat together the eggs, sugar, salt, and oil.', 'Stir in the flour and milk.', 'Pour batter into prepared pan.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.', 'Allow to cool.', 'To make the frosting: in a medium bowl, beat together the cream cheese and butter until smooth.', "Gradually beat in confectioners' sugar until smooth.", 'Spread over cooled cake.']

title: Coconut custard

recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Mix crumbs and butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch springform pan.', 'Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in large bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each just until blended.', 'Pour over crust.', 'Bake 50 min.', 'To 1 hour or until centre is almost set.', 'Run knife around rim of pan to loosen cake; cool before removing rim.', 'Refrigerate cheesecake 4 hours.', 'Microwave chocolate and milk in microwaveable bowl on high 1 min.', 'Or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring after 1 min.', 'Stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Cool 5 min.', '; pour over cheesecake.', 'Refrigerate 4 hours.']

title: Chocolate souffle
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees.', 'Butter a 2-quart souffle dish.', 'In a saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.', 'Remove from heat and stir in sugar, flour, cocoa, and salt.', 'Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.', 'Stir in vanilla.', 'Pour into prepared souffle dish.', 'Bake for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.', 'Cool completely.', "Dust with confectioners' sugar."]

title: Rice krispies treats
recipe: ['Microwave butter in large microwaveable bowl on high 45 sec.', 'Or until melted.', 'Add marshmallows; toss to coat.', 'Microwave 1-1/2 min.', 'Or until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is well blended, stirring after 45 sec.', 'Add cereal; mix well.', 'Press onto bottom of 13x9-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Cool.', 'Cut into 24 bars.']

title: Coconut cream sauce
recipe: ['In a medium saucepan, combine the coconut milk, cream, sugar and butter.', 'Bring to a boil over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.', 'Remove from the heat and stir in the vanilla.', 'Let cool slightly.', 'Transfer the sauce to a bowl and refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.']

title: The original recipe
recipe: ['Combine all of the ingredients except the ice in a cocktail shaker and shake vigorously for 10 seconds.', 'Add ice and shake again.', 'Strain into a chilled cocktail glass and garnish with the bitters.']

title: The original recipe
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a cocktail shaker and shake vigorously.', 'Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.']

title: Sofrito
recipe: ['Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add onions and garlic; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Stir in tomatoes, peppers and salt; cook 5 min.', 'Or until heated through, stirring occasionally.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Stir in cilantro.']

title: Caramelized peaches with cream
recipe: ['Preheat the oven to 350.', 'In a large bowl, toss the peaches with the sugar and salt.', 'Spread the peaches in a 9-by-13-inch baking dish and bake for about 1 hour, until tender and caramelized.', 'Let cool slightly, then peel and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.', 'In a medium bowl, whisk the eggs with the cream and butter.', 'Season with salt.', 'Pour the cream mixture over the peaches and bake for about 30 minutes, until the peaches are tender and the cream is bubbling.', 'Serve warm.']

title: Egg salad sandwich
recipe: ['Mix mayo and mustard in medium bowl.', 'Add eggs, onions and peppers; mix lightly.', 'Fill buns with lettuce and egg salad.']

title: Chickpea salad with radishes and tomatoes
recipe: ['Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.', 'Combine oil and vinegar in a small bowl, stirring with a whisk.', 'Drizzle dressing over salad; toss gently to coat.']

title: Crispy fried chicken
recipe: ['In a shallow dish, combine the flour, salt and pepper.', 'In another shallow dish, beat the egg.', 'In another shallow dish, combine the panko and panko.', 'Dip the chicken in the egg, then dredge in the panko mixture.', 'In a large skillet, heat the oil to 375.', 'Fry the chicken until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.', 'Drain on paper towels.']

title: Bacon wrapped cheese bites
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400 degrees f.', 'Cut cheese into 12 slices; cut each slice crosswise in half.', 'Wrap 1 bacon slice around each cheese cube; secure with wooden toothpicks.', 'Place, seam sides down, on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 10 min.', 'Or until bacon is crisp and cheese is melted.']

title: Easy swedish pancakes
recipe: ['In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, flour, sugar, and salt.', 'Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Pour about 1/4 cup of batter into the skillet, and cook until bubbles form and the edges are dry, about 2 minutes.', 'Flip and cook until browned on the other side, about 2 minutes more.', 'Repeat with remaining batter.']

title: Chocolate cheesecake cupcakes
recipe: ['Heat oven to 350f.', 'Line 24 muffin cups with paper baking cups; set aside.', 'Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwaveable bowl on high 2 min.', 'Or until butter is melted.', 'Stir until chocolate is completely melted.', 'Add sugar; mix well.', 'Blend in eggs and vanilla.', 'Add flour; mix well.', 'Spoon into prepared muffin cups.', 'Bake 20 to 25 min.', 'Or until toothpick inserted in centres comes out clean.', 'Cool in pans 10 min.', '; remove to wire racks.', 'Cool completely.', 'Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in large bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Add melted chocolate; mix well.', 'Pipe onto cupcakes.']

title: Roasted rosemary potatoes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 450 degrees f.', 'Wash and dry potatoes.', 'Cut potatoes into quarters.', 'Place potatoes in a large bowl.', 'Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat.', 'Sprinkle with rosemary, salt and pepper.', 'Place potatoes on a baking sheet and roast for 30 minutes.', 'Turn potatoes over and roast for another 20 minutes.']

title: Barbecue chicken wings
recipe: ['Heat barbecue to medium-high heat.', 'Mix barbecue sauce and pepper.', 'Reserve half the barbecue sauce mixture.', 'Grill chicken 15 min.', 'Or until done, turning and brushing occasionally with remaining barbecue sauce mixture.']

title: Chocolate chip ice cream
recipe: ['In a large bowl, whisk together the egg yolks, sugar, milk, vanilla and cream.', 'Pour the mixture into the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment.', 'Beat on medium speed until the mixture is thick and creamy, about 5 minutes.', 'Pour the mixture into a large bowl and stir in the chocolate.', 'Cover and freeze for at least 4 hours or overnight.', 'When ready to serve, scoop the ice cream into bowls and top with the chocolate shavings.']

title: Jell-o mint oreo pudding cups
recipe: ['Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.', 'Stir in cool whip and food coloring.', 'Spoon into 12 paper-lined medium muffin cups.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.', 'Top with marshmallows just before serving.']

title: Mint julep
recipe: ['In a large pitcher, combine the mint leaves, sugar and water.', 'Stir until the sugar is dissolved.', 'Add the ice cubes and stir until the ice is completely melted.', 'Serve immediately.']

title: Homemade salt
recipe: ['Mix all ingredients together.', 'Store in an airtight container.']

title: Easy fried rice
recipe: ['Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.', 'Add onions; cook and stir 5 min.', 'Or until crisp-tender.', 'Add rice, water and soy sauce; stir.', 'Bring to boil.', 'Cover; simmer on medium-low heat 5 min.', 'Remove from heat.', 'Let stand 5 min.', 'Fluff with fork.']

title: Crunchy cobb salad
recipe: ['Mix dressing and egg in large bowl.', 'Add all remaining ingredients except lettuce; mix lightly.', 'Serve on lettuce leaves.']

title: Grilled garlic marinade
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a bowl.', 'Add meat and marinate for at least 4 hours.', 'Grill or broil meat until done.']

title: Dilled green beans
recipe: ['Cook green beans in boiling water until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.', 'Drain and rinse with cold water.', 'Combine green beans, onion, dill, vinegar, oil, salt, and pepper in a large bowl.', 'Toss to coat.']

title: Berry cream cheese dessert
recipe: ['Beat cream cheese and sugar in medium bowl with mixer until blended.', 'Add berries; mix well.', 'Spoon into 2-qt.', 'Serving bowl.', 'Refrigerate 1 hour.', 'Meanwhile, mix water and pectin in small saucepan.', 'Bring to boil on high heat, stirring constantly.', 'Add to cream cheese mixture; stir 3 min.', 'Or until thickened.', 'Pour over berries in bowl; stir until well blended.']

title: Green beans with garlic and lemon
recipe: ['Cook beans in boiling water in large saucepan 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.', 'Drain.', 'Heat oil in same saucepan over medium heat.', 'Add garlic; cook 1 minute.', 'Add beans; cook 1 minute or until heated through.', 'Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.']
